description: Photos: Jackets are golden against the SEC in 2016
title: Photos: Jackets are golden against the SEC in 2016
title_page: Photos: Jackets are golden against the SEC in 2016
text:
1 / 13
HYOSUB SHIN / AJC/hshin@ajc.com Georgia Tech played three games against SEC opponents in 2016 and won all three. The Jackets beat Vanderbilt 38-7, Georgia 28-27 and Kentucky 33-18. Take a look at photos from all three games, including shots of coach Paul Johnson getting to shake hands as a victor after each one.
2 / 13
HYOSUB SHIN / AJC/hshin@ajc.com VANDERBILT: Yellow Jackets celebrate their victory over the Commmodores on September 17, 2016. Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets won 38-7.

HYOSUB SHIN / AJC/hshin@ajc.com VANDERBILT: Qua Searcy (1) celebrates with fans after Georgia Tech beat Vanderbilt 38-7 at Bobby Dodd Stadium on Saturday, September 17, 2016.
4 / 13
HYOSUB SHIN / AJC/hshin@ajc.com VANDERBILT: Tech coach Paul Johnson waves to fans aftera 38-7 win over the Commodores on Saturday, September 17, 2016.

HYOSUB SHIN / AJC/hshin@ajc.com VANDERBILT: Georgia Tech's Clinton Lynch (22) celebrates with teammates after he scored a touchdown in the second half on September 17, 2016. The Yellow Jackets won 38-7.

HYOSUB SHIN / AJC/hshin@ajc.com GEORGIA: Qua Searcy (1) leaps over for a game-winning touchdown in the second half at Sanford Stadium on Saturday, November 26, 2016. Georgia Tech won 28-27.

HYOSUB SHIN / AJC/hshin@ajc.com GEORGIA: Kicker Harrison Butker (87) and other players celebrate with pieces of the Sanford Stadium hedges after their 28-27 win over Georgia on Saturday, November 26, 2016.
